where ε (38 for anatase30)—the dielectric constant of titania, ε0 (8.85 × 10–12 F/m)—the vacuum permittivity, e (1.602 × 10–19 C)—the electron charge, and E—the applied potential. For the calculations, the geometric surface area and the same dielectric constant for all of the investigated samples were used. The position of the flat-band potential was indicated as the potential where the tangent to the M–S plot intersects with potential axis for CSC−2 = 0.
